  <slide>
    <title>Keyboard Testing</title>
    <contents>
      <table class="table table-striped table-hover">
        <caption>Keyboard Testing Commands</caption>
        <thead>
          <th>Key</th>
          <th>Expected Behaviors for Accessibility</th>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Tab<br/>Shift-Tab</td>
            <td>
              <ul>
                <li>Use the "TAB" key to move focus between links, form controls and custom widgets on a web page.</li>
                <li>Verify you can see which element has the focus.</li>
                <li>If it is a link read the link text to make sure it describes the target of the link.</li>
              </ul>
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Space<br/>Return/Enter</td>
            <td>
              <ul>
                <li>"Space" or "Return/Enter" key activates links and buttons, or chages the state of checkboxes  or radio buttons.</li>
              </ul>
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Cursor Keys</td>
            <td>
              <ul>
                <li>For menus of links or actions do the cursor keys allow you to move keyboard focus between items.</li>
              </ul>
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Skip to Main</td>
            <td>
              <ul>
                <li>Is there a way to "skip to" main content?</li>
              </ul>
            </td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </contents>
